<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="87" type="type protologue">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Type protologue.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="87">
Ad fontes calidos Araschan Bulak in Turkestania occidentali, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Krause</emphasis>
s.n. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Type</emphasis>
: Taschkenter Alatau, Araschan Bulak, 11 Jun 1871, (
<taxonomicName genus="Hieronymous" lsidName="Hieronymous" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Hieronymous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Krause</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype: LE [only one collection cited]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="87" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was applied by several authors to small densely tufted alpine annual plants of south-central and southwest Asia, which we recognise as 
<taxonomicName genus="P." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="P. diaphora var. alpina" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="variety" species="diaphora" variety="alpina">P. diaphora var. alpina</taxonomicName>
(based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">Poa persica var. alpina</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier [1884]</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="Botaniceski Zurnal (Moscow &amp; Leningrad)" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" refId="B67" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1976. Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1-788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" title="Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1 - 788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" year="1976">Tzvelev (1976</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 480) noted that the holotype collection of 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared to be a mix of 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">altaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="diaphora" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="diaphora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">diaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="songarica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="songarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">songarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms (&quot;p.p. max&quot; = 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. songarica" family="Poaceae" genus="E." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="songarica">E. altaica subsp. songarica</taxonomicName>
, somewhat intermediate between this subsp. and subsp. 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="altaica">altaica</taxonomicName>
, and &quot;p.p. minor&quot; = 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. altaica" family="Poaceae" genus="E." infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica" subspecies="altaica">E. altaica subsp. altaica</taxonomicName>
); he considered 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="altaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">E. altaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subsp. 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="species" subspecies="songarica">songarica</taxonomicName>
. Further study is needed to clarifiy the placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and determine if it is synonymous with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." infraspecific-rank="var." lsidName="P. diaphora var. alpina" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" rank="variety" species="diaphora" variety="alpina">P. diaphora var. alpina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
